5:
It seems we've lost our pursuers. But 
we cannot go on like this for—
12:
I'm fine... There is nothing... to worry 
about…
16:
...I'm gonna find a place to hide! 
Wait for me!
21:
We'll be able to rest here tonight. 
But the problem is food.
24:
That's the last of our supplies.
*sigh* Things aren't looking too good...
27: What do we do now, Light?
32:
We keep going underground, seeking 
the Cradle. What other choice is left to 
us, with no guide?
36: Maybe... I SHOULD turn myself in.
40:
I've been thinking about what Regis 
said... About how the Administrator's 
angry because you took me away 
from her.
42:
I thought I could be the solution to 
everything, but... I was the problem 
all along…
49:
Hey, listen. We'd have been toast a 
long time ago, if you hadn't been there 
for us.
52:
Yeah. And I know that type. Once she's 
developed a thirst for vengeance, she 
won't stop 'til she's tasted blood.
54:
...Dia. Why is she so obsessed with 
you?
58: You said that voices were held sacred...
62:
Yeah, but it doesn't have to be that 
way.
63:
To droids, a voice is just like any other 
part. Exchangeable.
65:
The Administrator could replicate my 
voice. She could give it to someone 
else. But she won't.
70:
She probably misses the time when 
humans still lived on this planet, and 
they sang about things like joy and 
love and sadness... Music brought 
them together.
71:
So she decided that voices... 
are irreplaceable.
78:
She summons me when she can't 
sleep. All I do is sing her lullabies…
82: I'd like... to hear a lullaby...
92: Why not? Beats singing for that witch.
97:
B-but we're in danger... And Stella's 
sick, and—
103:
And music will help ease the pain. 
Will you not sing for her?
130:
Wow. That was great! It kind of made 
me feel nostalgic, if you know what I 
mean, but... yeah! I'm blown away!
136:
You really think so?
...If I were to sing on your planet... you 
think people would want to listen?
150:
Wait... I recognize him... From the Lost 
City! What's he doing here?
160:
Don't... stop... P-p-please, no. Don't 
throw me away!
168:
I won't. I won't let anyone throw you 
away.
178:
He wishes for us to follow him... 
But where?
181:
The place where music died and droids 
were born…
183:
The Cradle.
That... is what he said.
